    <h2>Collecting and Using Your Personal Data</h2>
    <h3>Types of Data Collected</h3>
    <p><b>Personal Data:</b> We may ask You to provide certain personally identifiable information that can be used to contact or identify You.</p>
    <p><b>Usage Data:</b> Collected automatically when using the Service. Includes IP address, browser type, pages visited, device identifiers, and diagnostics.</p>

    <h2>Wallet Data and Security</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>We do not collect, store, or have access to your private keys, recovery phrase, or any data related to your transactions.</li>
      <li>All sensitive information is stored locally on your device only and remains fully under your control.</li>
      <li>If you lose your recovery phrase, we will not be able to restore or recover your wallet.</li>
      <li>Your funds are 100% self-custodial — Bitnova never takes custody.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Use of Your Personal Data</h2>
    <p>We may use Personal Data for:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>To provide and maintain our Service.</li>
      <li>To manage Your Account and registration.</li>
      <li>To perform contractual obligations.</li>
      <li>To contact You (email, phone, SMS).</li>
      <li>To provide updates, news, or offers (unless opted out).</li>
      <li>To respond to inquiries and manage requests.</li>
      <li>For business transfers (merger, acquisition, or asset sale).</li>
      <li><b>Additional:</b> To detect, prevent, and address fraud or security issues.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Retention of Your Personal Data</h2>
    <p>The Company will retain Your Personal Data only as long as necessary for the purposes in this Privacy Policy. Usage Data may be retained longer for security or functionality improvements, or as required by law.</p>

    <h2>Transfer of Your Personal Data</h2>
    <p>Your data may be transferred to and maintained on computers outside of Your jurisdiction. By using the Service, You consent to such transfers, with safeguards in place.</p>

    <h2>Delete Your Personal Data</h2>
    <p>You may delete or request deletion of Your Personal Data at any time. Contact us at <a href="mailto:support@Bitnova.app">support@Bitnova.app</a>. Some data may be retained as required by law.</p>

    <h2>Your Privacy Rights (GDPR/CCPA)</h2>
    <p>Depending on your location, you may have rights under data protection laws such as GDPR or CCPA, including:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Request access to your data.</li>
      <li>Request correction or deletion.</li>
      <li>Object to processing of your data.</li>
      <li>Data portability rights.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Disclosure of Your Personal Data</h2>
    <p>The Company may disclose Personal Data in the good faith belief that it is necessary to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Comply with a legal obligation.</li>
      <li>Protect rights or property.</li>
      <li>Prevent wrongdoing or fraudulent activity.</li>
      <li>Protect the safety of Users or the public.</li>
